Discovering novel therapies for treatment resistant depression and other dopamine-related diseases
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Since our founding in 2009, our mission at PharmoRx Therapeutics, Inc. (PTI) has been to create pharmaceutical therapies for treating dopamine-related central nervous system (CNS) diseases.    Depression has continued to challenge the medical community in recent decades. Although there are some known treatments for depression, the relapse rates are unacceptably high, and new treatment options are desperately needed.    What we are doing is crucial for 350 million patients, as depression is the leading cause of disability worldwide. The burden of depression and other mental health conditions is on the rise globally.    Our first quest is to develop a medication for Treatment Resistant Depression (TRD), a disease that affects approximately 4.8 million people in the US, and over 17 million throughout the world. A successful cure continues to elude our industry and these millions of patients, despite billions of dollars of investment by some of the brightest minds and development teams in our industry.    Based on research and clinical results to date, we believe that we have found the key that unlocks the door to a successful therapy for TRD, as well as a promising platform for other diseases such as Major Depressive Disorder (MDD), Depression in Parkinson’s, and Impulsive Compulsive Disorders (ICD).   With our patented pharmacologic innovation and further clinical development, we intend to restore a happy and productive life to millions of people afflicted with TRD, MDD, ICD and other CNS diseases. PTI is currently raising up to $15M to conduct the Phase 2b study in TRD as well as clinical work and a Phase 2a study in BED.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Selegnapath is a brand protection agency with a mission to assist brands in safeguarding themselves and their customers. The agency focuses on identifying and shutting down unauthorized sellers and provides support in cases of intellectual property infringement. Strategies and approaches are employed to ensure alignment with clients' brand protection plans, facilitating the identification and elimination of risks at every stage of a product's lifecycle. Selegnapath offers its expertise whether clients are initiating brand protection efforts or expanding existing programs. The agency's team is skilled in developing plans to locate and address companies, individuals, distributors, and DBAs engaged in the unauthorized sale and misuse of products. Services include issuing cease and desist letters and requesting information about product sources when uncertainty arises. Selegnapath provides personalized support, allowing clients to update information on new resellers, trusted distributor relationships, or decisions regarding authorized resellers on 3P marketplaces. In more serious cases, Selegnapath can compile comprehensive reports for each situation and deliver them to clients' attorneys for potential litigation, providing support as needed. The agency's proactive approach enables the identification of typical behavior patterns in unauthorized sellers. Selegnapath's overarching objective, through the Selegnapath plan, is to enhance sales and the brand experience by eradicating unauthorized sellers. The agency is committed to investigating and taking action against any infringements of clients' intellectual property, with monitoring solutions that keep clients updated on the latest infringements and provide necessary information for action.
